    • Enum Constant Detail

      • owner

        public static final IpcTagKey owner
        The library that produced the metric.

      • result

        public static final IpcTagKey result
        Indicates whether or not the request was successful. See IpcResult for permitted values.

      • errorGroup

        public static final IpcTagKey errorGroup
        Dimension indicating a high level cause for the request failure. These groups are the same for all implementations to make it easier to query across all services and client implementations. See IpcErrorGroup for permitted values.

      • errorReason

        public static final IpcTagKey errorReason
        Implementation specific error code.

      • attempt

        public static final IpcTagKey attempt
        Indicates the attempt number for the request.

      • attemptFinal

        public static final IpcTagKey attemptFinal
        Indicates if this is the final attempt for the request. For example, if the client is configured to allow 1 retry, then the second attempt would be final. Acceptable values are true and false.

      • id

        public static final IpcTagKey id
        Identifier for the client instance making the request. This is typically the name used to see the associated configuration settings for the client.

      • vip

        public static final IpcTagKey vip
        Eureka VIP used to select the server. If there are multiple vips in the list, then it should be the first vip that caused the server to get selected.

      • endpoint

        public static final IpcTagKey endpoint
        The server side endpoint that is being requested. This should be a bounded set that will have a small cardinality. Do not pass in the unsanitized path value for a URI.

      • protocol

        public static final IpcTagKey protocol
        Protocol used for the request. For example http_1 or http_2.

      • clientRegion

        public static final IpcTagKey clientRegion
        Region where the client is located.

      • clientZone

        public static final IpcTagKey clientZone
        Availability zone where the client is located.

      • clientApp

        public static final IpcTagKey clientApp
        Application that is running the client.

      • clientCluster

        public static final IpcTagKey clientCluster
        Cluster that is running the client.

      • clientAsg

        public static final IpcTagKey clientAsg
        Server group that is running the client.

      • serverRegion

        public static final IpcTagKey serverRegion
        Region where the server is located.

      • serverZone

        public static final IpcTagKey serverZone
        Availability zone where the server is located.

      • serverApp

        Application name for the server.

      • serverCluster

        public static final IpcTagKey serverCluster
        Cluster name for the server.

      • serverAsg

        public static final IpcTagKey serverAsg
        Server group name for the server.

      • serverNode

        public static final IpcTagKey serverNode
        Instance id for the server. Do not use this unless you know it will not cause a metrics explosion. If there is any doubt, then do not enable it.

      • serverPort

        public static final IpcTagKey serverPort
        The port number connected to on the server.

      • httpStatus

        public static final IpcTagKey httpStatus
        HTTP status code.

      • httpMethod
